[Student "S"]
{SOUTH makes a Negative Double rather than responding 1\S to indicate he has just a 4-card suit.

NORTH has four \Ss so she bids 1\S, showing a minimum opener.

With 11 points SOUTH makes an invitational bid of 3\S but NORTH declines the invitation by passing.}

